description: The process of detecting profile object type mapping by using given objects.

parameters.name: Objects
parameters.description: A string that is serialized from a JSON object. (string) ---

parameters.name: DomainName
parameters.description: The unique name of the domain.

nested_items.name: DetectedProfileObjectTypes
nested_items.description: Detected ProfileObjectType mappings from given objects. A maximum of one mapping is supported.

nested_items.name: SourceLastUpdatedTimestampFormat
nested_items.description: The format of sourceLastUpdatedTimestamp that was detected in fields.

nested_items.name: Source
nested_items.description: A field of a ProfileObject. For example: _source.FirstName, where '_source' is a ProfileObjectType of a Zendesk user and 'FirstName' is a field in that ObjectType.

nested_items.name: Target
nested_items.description: The location of the data in the standard ProfileObject model. For example: _profile.Address.PostalCode.

nested_items.name: ContentType
nested_items.description: The content type of the field. Used for determining equality when searching.

nested_items.name: StandardIdentifiers
nested_items.description: The types of keys that a ProfileObject can have. Each ProfileObject can have only 1 UNIQUE key but multiple PROFILE keys. PROFILE, ASSET, CASE, or ORDER means that this key can be used to tie an object to a PROFILE, ASSET, CASE, or ORDER respectively. UNIQUE means that it can be used to uniquely identify an object. If a key a is marked as SECONDARY, it will be used to search for profiles after all other PROFILE keys have been searched. A LOOKUP_ONLY key is only used to match a profile but is not persisted to be used for searching of the profile. A NEW_ONLY key is only used if the profile does not already exist before the object is ingested, otherwise it is only used for matching objects to profiles.

nested_items.name: FieldNames
nested_items.description: The reference for the key name of the fields map.
